Reasoning: The paper deals with game theory and voting models, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The use of iterative algorithms and convergence results suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The classification of convergence results based on the order of players and better-reply strategies may also involve the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on acyclic games and game forms may relate to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
